1
00:00:00,453 --> 00:00:01,766
(Episode 4:
Second Time's the Charm for Naps)

2
00:00:01,766 --> 00:00:04,500
Crash!

3
00:00:06,166 --> 00:00:07,400
Are you sleepy? Wait.

4
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:10,233
Are you sleepy?

5
00:00:10,234 --> 00:00:11,432
(Sleepy, fussy Yu Jun)

6
00:00:11,433 --> 00:00:12,366
What should I say?

7
00:00:13,133 --> 00:00:14,366
Do you want to take a nap?

8
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:16,733
Isn't it about time?
Should we make him take a nap?

9
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:17,533
I think so.

10
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:22,000
Maybe it's because you're pushing
from this side.

11
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,600
Shouldn't we check when he's standing?

12
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:24,433
Yes.

13
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:26,000
I don't smell it.

14
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,366
But it's bulging in front.

15
00:00:28,366 --> 00:00:30,033
- Should we change it, then?
- Yes.

16
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:31,166
Yu Jun!

17
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:32,733
- I'll do this, and you can change it.
- Yes, do it.

18
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:33,933
We'll take his pants off when he's up.

19
00:00:33,933 --> 00:00:35,133
When he goes up.

20
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:37,300
In 1, 2, 3!

21
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:39,166
Hooray!

22
00:00:39,166 --> 00:00:41,133
- Make sure he's distracted.
- It's exciting, right?

23
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:42,400
Can you change it while standing?

24
00:00:42,966 --> 00:00:44,433
No, we need to lay him down.

25
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:47,500
No, just keep going
until I take off his diaper.

26
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,100
Can you do it?

27
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:50,566
(SOOBIN Air is taking off again.)

28
00:00:50,566 --> 00:00:52,400
Where do you want to go, Yu Jun?
To the US?

29
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:54,766
(Let's go!)

30
00:00:56,233 --> 00:00:58,533
(His diaper has come off
before reaching the US.)

31
00:00:58,533 --> 00:01:01,966
(The new diaper is waiting for him
right there.)

32
00:01:03,866 --> 00:01:06,500
(Will they succeed at changing diapers
without him crying?)

33
00:01:06,966 --> 00:01:08,000
This is so much fun!

34
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,100
Aren't you having a blast?

35
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:12,166
In 1, 2, 3!

36
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:14,450
- Right on!
- Yes!

37
00:01:14,451 --> 00:01:16,733
(They made it to stop his tears
with a high-five.)

38
00:01:16,733 --> 00:01:18,500
(Or not!)

39
00:01:19,100 --> 00:01:21,700
(We can't make him cry!)

40
00:01:23,300 --> 00:01:24,200
Are you having fun?

41
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,533
(Yu Jun almost cried, but stopped.)

42
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:30,366
(Sacrificing their joints
just to change his diaper)

43
00:01:30,366 --> 00:01:31,833
How exciting!

44
00:01:32,266 --> 00:01:34,100
(This is so much fun!)

45
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,566
- Good boy!
- There we go!

46
00:01:35,566 --> 00:01:37,000
Let's just put your pants on.

47
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,400
One leg at a time.

48
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:40,000
We changed his diaper without him crying!

49
00:01:41,066 --> 00:01:42,733
- I'm so proud of us.
- Good boy!

50
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:44,500
(Will they even succeed
at making him fall asleep?)

51
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,700
- He's happy today.
- For sure.

52
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:49,000
Are you sleepy?

53
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:50,466
- You are!
- You're sleepy!

54
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:52,066
(I like it here.)

55
00:01:52,066 --> 00:01:53,533
You've been chosen this time.

56
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:55,333
Let's give him his pacifier.

57
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:57,433
What is Yu Jun wearing right now?

58
00:01:57,433 --> 00:01:58,633
Let's give him a matching pacifier.

59
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,266
That's clever.

60
00:02:01,066 --> 00:02:03,033
This is already set up,
so let's just give him the white one.

61
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:04,566
Open up, Yu Jun!

62
00:02:04,566 --> 00:02:05,600
There we go!

63
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:13,066
(Yu Jun's nap time)

64
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:18,766
(There's honey dripping
from HUENINGKAI's eyes.)

65
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:25,733
(It's HUENINGKAI's first time
putting Yu Jun to bed.)

66
00:02:28,966 --> 00:02:31,200
(Sparkling eyes)

67
00:02:33,133 --> 00:02:37,700
(Weren't you sleepy just now?)

68
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:41,333
(Meanwhile, in the living room)

69
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:44,600
(Where are BEOMGYU and TAEHYUN?)

70
00:02:45,633 --> 00:02:46,566
It's light.

71
00:02:46,566 --> 00:02:47,733
(Setting up Yu Jun's car seat)

72
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:49,066
It's not heavy at all.

73
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,233
All the way in.

74
00:02:52,033 --> 00:02:53,000
- Okay.
- All the way.

75
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,700
It goes this way.

76
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:57,066
- All done.
- Push it all the way!

77
00:02:57,066 --> 00:02:58,033
Keep pushing!

78
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:01,700
(For Yu Jun's safety)

79
00:03:01,866 --> 00:03:03,366
Hey, Yu Jun!

80
00:03:03,766 --> 00:03:07,333
We'll give him an airplane ride
all the way here.

81
00:03:07,666 --> 00:03:09,000
We have to clip it to this.

82
00:03:10,133 --> 00:03:11,400
Click.

83
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,966
- All done.
- Ready!

84
00:03:12,966 --> 00:03:14,300
Then, just undo this buckle.

85
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:16,266
- Right on!
- Perfect.

86
00:03:16,266 --> 00:03:17,266
Let's put Yu Jun to bed.

87
00:03:17,266 --> 00:03:18,700
(Is Yu Jun sleeping by now?)

88
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:21,800
(No.)

89
00:03:22,433 --> 00:03:27,333
(HUENINGKAI walked around for a while
with Yu Jun in his arms.)

90
00:03:29,366 --> 00:03:31,533
(Tickling him)

91
00:03:32,133 --> 00:03:35,300
(Back scratches as a bonus)

92
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:38,833
(Let's go.)

93
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:44,900
(Yu Jun's eyes are open wide
and not interested in sleeping at all.)

94
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,100
(Is he still up?)

95
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:50,933
(Bed Number One is setting off to help.)

96
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:54,700
(Bed Number Two)

97
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,400
Do you want to give me a chance?

98
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,966
- Go to this uncle.
- I'll be good to you. I promise.

99
00:04:00,966 --> 00:04:03,233
I'll be really good, okay?

100
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:04,066
Here.

101
00:04:04,066 --> 00:04:05,566
- Sorry, Yu Jun!
- I got you.

102
00:04:05,566 --> 00:04:09,000
I'm sorry, Yu Jun!

103
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:11,433
(Bed Number Two! Where are you going?)

104
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:13,333
(Bed Number Two is recovering.)

105
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:15,566
I'm sorry!

106
00:04:20,766 --> 00:04:22,395
I'm not so bad
now that you think about it, right?

107
00:04:23,366 --> 00:04:24,700
(Yes, you're not too bad.)

108
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:25,954
You're embarrassed by crying, right?

109
00:04:27,766 --> 00:04:30,866
(Round Two of the napping attempt)

110
00:04:35,266 --> 00:04:36,100
Yu Jun.

111
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:37,433
Here.

112
00:04:37,933 --> 00:04:41,733
(Hugging him in the perfect position
to lean on him and sleep)

113
00:04:50,066 --> 00:04:54,500
(Slowly leaning on SOOBIN's shoulder)

114
00:04:55,833 --> 00:05:00,066
(Much better patting than last time)

115
00:05:05,566 --> 00:05:08,133
(About to fall asleep)

116
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:18,233
(SOOBIN's version
of "Merry-Go-Round of Life")

117
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,533
(Squirming)

118
00:05:21,233 --> 00:05:25,000
(The 14-month-old's last efforts
not to fall asleep)

119
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:30,433
(SOOBIN: "Please...")

120
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:39,000
(Yu Jun's eyes are slowly closing.)

121
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:51,566
(Please let Yu Jun have a nice nap.)

122
00:05:58,566 --> 00:05:59,633
Is he still up?

123
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:01,433
Or is he sleeping?

124
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:03,566
Is he up?

125
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:08,033
(Just hold on for a bit longer.)

126
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:17,033
(The best part about Yu Jun napping)

127
00:06:17,033 --> 00:06:18,966
(Soft sighs)

128
00:06:19,366 --> 00:06:23,833
(You can listen to Yu Jun's breaths
up close.)

129
00:06:35,366 --> 00:06:40,433
(Yu Jun is finally fast asleep.)

130
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:54,633
(Continuing to pat him
until he falls deeper asleep)

131
00:06:56,533 --> 00:07:01,033
(Congratulations,
you succeeded at making Yu Jun nap!)

132
00:07:02,966 --> 00:07:05,066
Is he sleeping now?

133
00:07:06,133 --> 00:07:09,866
(Checking one more time)

134
00:07:09,866 --> 00:07:13,933
(The hardest part is laying him down
while he's sleeping.)

135
00:07:18,033 --> 00:07:21,766
(First attempt at laying him down)

136
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:29,766
(He failed.)

137
00:07:33,966 --> 00:07:37,500
(Second attempt at laying him down)

138
00:07:39,033 --> 00:07:44,433
(Please be careful! He might wake up!)

139
00:07:48,366 --> 00:07:50,966
(Failing again)

140
00:07:52,721 --> 00:07:55,600
I got you. Sorry.

141
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,033
I used too much force, didn't I?

142
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:05,700
(Putting him back to sleep
since he's woken up)

143
00:08:06,566 --> 00:08:09,600
(A step back for a bigger step forward)

144
00:08:13,366 --> 00:08:14,366
(Drowsy)

145
00:08:14,366 --> 00:08:16,266
(Laughing)

146
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:21,166
(Third attempt at laying him down)

147
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:27,600
(Failing again, of course)

148
00:08:29,233 --> 00:08:33,666
(SOOBIN seems a bit scared this time.)

149
00:08:35,266 --> 00:08:37,900
(Fourth attempt at laying him down)

150
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:42,633
(I'll be brave and careful this time.)

151
00:08:42,633 --> 00:08:44,366
(A huge failure)

152
00:08:44,366 --> 00:08:46,466
I can't lay him down!

153
00:08:47,633 --> 00:08:49,266
I can't lay Yu Jun down.

154
00:08:50,533 --> 00:08:51,700
Do you just want to sleep in my arms?

155
00:08:54,533 --> 00:08:58,900
(He kind of succeeded
since Yu Jun is sleeping anyway.)

156
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:02,866
(Carefully sitting)

157
00:09:02,866 --> 00:09:07,066
(SOOBIN has decided to be
Yu Jun's human bed.)

158
00:09:14,433 --> 00:09:17,866
(Looking like he's had a rough battle
against nap time)

159
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:28,900
(Punching)

160
00:09:29,933 --> 00:09:35,166
(Babysitters don't get surprised
by the sudden punches.)

161
00:09:36,366 --> 00:09:40,666
(What is Yu Jun dreaming about?)

162
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:44,366
(Oh! I see my snacks flying!)

163
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:53,333
(The human bed fell asleep
while trying to make Yu Jun sleep.)

164
00:09:55,900 --> 00:10:00,100
(Have a good nap.)

165
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:05,800
(Sleep tight to those
in the living room too.)

166
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,533
(Tossing and turning)

167
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:14,367
(Yu Jun woke up for a moment.)

168
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:18,010
(Pacifier in his mouth)

169
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:20,833
(SOOBIN's carousel runs again.)

170
00:10:21,552 --> 00:10:23,352
(Is he feeling hot?)

171
00:10:23,352 --> 00:10:24,619
(Blowing)

172
00:10:24,619 --> 00:10:27,585
(Blowing air with his mouth)

173
00:10:28,588 --> 00:10:32,885
(There was a bit of a crisis,)

174
00:10:33,552 --> 00:10:38,119
(but Yu Jun, and SOOBIN,
who ended up being his bed...)

175
00:10:40,419 --> 00:10:44,819
(fell right into a good two hours
of sleep.)

176
00:10:47,552 --> 00:10:50,052
(TAEHYUN woke up early,)

177
00:10:50,052 --> 00:10:52,319
(and now he's filming SOOBIN sleeping!)

178
00:10:52,952 --> 00:10:55,019
(Smooth camera movement)

179
00:10:55,719 --> 00:10:57,985
(He doesn't forget to take a photo.)

180
00:10:59,085 --> 00:11:00,752
(Feeling proud)

181
00:11:01,352 --> 00:11:03,585
(What will TAEHYUN do
while everyone is asleep?)

182
00:11:04,152 --> 00:11:07,019
(Checking the childcare diary)

183
00:11:08,052 --> 00:11:09,885
(He found out what to do.)

184
00:11:10,719 --> 00:11:14,452
(Preparing some fruit
for Yu Jun in advance)

185
00:11:15,652 --> 00:11:18,052
(Cut the small strawberries in half
and the larger ones into eighths.)

186
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:19,319
(Cut the ripe bananas into this size.)

187
00:11:19,319 --> 00:11:21,185
(Put them in a bowl to feed with a fork
or let him eat on his own.)

188
00:11:21,485 --> 00:11:24,319
(Yu Jun's fruit snack is ready.)

189
00:11:26,719 --> 00:11:28,285
(Is Yu Jun awake?)

190
00:11:28,285 --> 00:11:29,919
What is it? Did you wake up?

191
00:11:31,552 --> 00:11:32,685
Do you want to wake up?

192
00:11:33,585 --> 00:11:35,519
(Wiggling)

193
00:11:35,952 --> 00:11:36,985
What's wrong?

194
00:11:36,985 --> 00:11:39,985
(3:15 p.m., Yu Jun wakes up.)

195
00:11:41,519 --> 00:11:42,519
Okay.

196
00:11:42,519 --> 00:11:43,585
(TAEHYUN checks if Yu Jun is awake.)

197
00:11:45,419 --> 00:11:48,852
(A pacifier for fussiness)

198
00:11:50,219 --> 00:11:54,385
I've got some fruit ready
for when he wakes up.

199
00:11:55,152 --> 00:11:56,319
You did all these?

200
00:11:56,819 --> 00:11:58,552
- Thank you.
- I prepared them.

201
00:11:58,552 --> 00:12:00,185
You put him to sleep,
so I should at least do this.

202
00:12:01,185 --> 00:12:02,185
Wait.

203
00:12:02,185 --> 00:12:03,185
(BEOMGYU and HUENINGKAI
also wake up with Yu Jun.)

204
00:12:03,185 --> 00:12:05,785
- Wait. I can't change his position.
- Did you sleep well, Yu Jun?

205
00:12:06,219 --> 00:12:08,156
Yu Jun looks so relaxed.

206
00:12:08,552 --> 00:12:10,519
- He was so tired?
- He looks so relaxed.

207
00:12:10,519 --> 00:12:11,519
He does?

208
00:12:11,852 --> 00:12:13,552
I recorded you while you were sleeping.

209
00:12:14,419 --> 00:12:15,485
- Really?
- Yes.

210
00:12:17,652 --> 00:12:18,785
I was sleeping with my jaw open.

211
00:12:18,785 --> 00:12:20,419
(A beautiful two-shot)

212
00:12:21,119 --> 00:12:22,219
Yu Jun, high five.

213
00:12:22,819 --> 00:12:24,473
- Good job!
- Wow.

214
00:12:27,552 --> 00:12:29,485
(I want the pacifier out.)

215
00:12:29,485 --> 00:12:30,519
What's this?

216
00:12:30,519 --> 00:12:31,552
He took it out.

217
00:12:31,919 --> 00:12:32,919
We can feed him now.

218
00:12:33,685 --> 00:12:35,019
- Say, ah.
- Say, ah.

219
00:12:35,019 --> 00:12:36,552
This looks delicious!

220
00:12:36,552 --> 00:12:37,885
You're so stubborn.

221
00:12:37,885 --> 00:12:39,052
That looks so good.

222
00:12:39,485 --> 00:12:41,585
(My strawberry!)

223
00:12:41,585 --> 00:12:44,519
(The strawberry tastes good.)

224
00:12:44,852 --> 00:12:46,185
Ah? Do you want it too?

225
00:12:46,752 --> 00:12:47,819
- Say, ah.
- Say, ah.

226
00:12:47,819 --> 00:12:48,819
(I don't want it.)

227
00:12:48,819 --> 00:12:51,719
So you couldn't put him down on the bed,
so you just slept together?

228
00:12:51,719 --> 00:12:53,419
No, I couldn't.

229
00:12:54,185 --> 00:12:56,185
Yu Jun!

230
00:12:56,185 --> 00:12:57,385
He woke up even when I moved a little.

231
00:12:57,385 --> 00:12:58,719
Here's a cracker!

232
00:12:59,852 --> 00:13:00,852
Yummy?

233
00:13:01,352 --> 00:13:02,352
So cute.

234
00:13:02,419 --> 00:13:03,419
(Half asleep and fussy)

235
00:13:03,419 --> 00:13:04,719
Let's put you down, Yu Jun.

236
00:13:05,585 --> 00:13:07,452
(No!)

237
00:13:08,885 --> 00:13:11,419
(I don't want to let him go.)

238
00:13:11,419 --> 00:13:12,519
It's okay. You can do it.

239
00:13:12,719 --> 00:13:13,785
You've got this.

240
00:13:13,785 --> 00:13:15,785
(They raise him to be tough.)

241
00:13:16,319 --> 00:13:17,385
See? You can do it.

242
00:13:17,819 --> 00:13:19,019
You can't give up milk.

243
00:13:19,019 --> 00:13:20,519
(Drinking milk while holding onto his bed)

244
00:13:20,519 --> 00:13:21,519
Delicious, right?

245
00:13:21,552 --> 00:13:22,719
Yu Jun, do you want one more?

246
00:13:22,985 --> 00:13:24,285
- Do you want to try this too?
- Yu Jun.

247
00:13:24,852 --> 00:13:26,552
(I'm not eating anymore.)

248
00:13:27,752 --> 00:13:28,752
(It's dangerous outside the bed.)

249
00:13:28,752 --> 00:13:29,852
Yu Jun, open up.

250
00:13:30,052 --> 00:13:31,085
Here.

251
00:13:32,785 --> 00:13:34,552
- Why isn't he eating?
- I don't think he wants to.

252
00:13:34,552 --> 00:13:36,552
(Yu Jun is not eating? Then BEOMGYU will.)

253
00:13:36,552 --> 00:13:37,552
I guess he's not in the mood to eat.

254
00:13:37,552 --> 00:13:38,552
(It's delicious.)

255
00:13:38,552 --> 00:13:39,552
Let's go out, Yu Jun.

256
00:13:39,752 --> 00:13:41,819
- Let's go out.
- Let's just get our things and go.

257
00:13:41,819 --> 00:13:42,819
(4:00 p.m., to uncles' workplace)

258
00:13:42,819 --> 00:13:44,419
Off to our homeground!

259
00:13:44,419 --> 00:13:45,419
Let's go.

260
00:13:47,519 --> 00:13:48,619
What's Yu Jun doing?

261
00:13:49,252 --> 00:13:50,252
Looking out the window.

262
00:13:51,019 --> 00:13:52,985
- Is he looking outside?
- Yes, I guess he likes the sunset.

263
00:13:53,052 --> 00:13:55,752
Right, we can give Yu Jun a pacifier
when he's in the car.

264
00:13:56,485 --> 00:13:58,785
Let's give it to him
when he's in a bad mood.

265
00:13:58,785 --> 00:13:59,785
Okay.

266
00:14:01,352 --> 00:14:04,619
(The car went quiet before they knew it.)

267
00:14:04,619 --> 00:14:06,752
(I miss my mom.)

268
00:14:06,752 --> 00:14:09,019
(I wonder what Dad is doing.)

269
00:14:09,919 --> 00:14:10,952
(Yu Jun is suddenly sad.)

270
00:14:10,952 --> 00:14:14,952
(Tearing up)

271
00:14:14,952 --> 00:14:16,019
(Is Yu Jun okay?)

272
00:14:16,019 --> 00:14:17,019
(Startled)

273
00:14:17,019 --> 00:14:19,219
(He's fine.)

274
00:14:20,419 --> 00:14:25,652
(I don't think I'm okay, Uncle.)

275
00:14:33,985 --> 00:14:37,685
(HUENINGKAI looks for something
in the baby bag.)

276
00:14:40,685 --> 00:14:41,719
Do you want a pacifier?

277
00:14:42,285 --> 00:14:43,752
- Why? Is he about to cry?
- Yes.

278
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:47,719
We should turn the air conditioner on.

279
00:14:48,252 --> 00:14:49,285
I think he's feeling hot.

280
00:14:49,285 --> 00:14:50,285
(Handshaking to thank him)

281
00:14:50,285 --> 00:14:52,519
(Peace is restored with the pacifier.)

282
00:14:53,019 --> 00:14:54,519
- Ta-da!
- Ta-da!

283
00:14:54,519 --> 00:14:56,652
- Here we are.
- This is where we work.

284
00:14:56,652 --> 00:14:57,785
(Yu Jun and the uncles gather
in the practice room for the comeback.)

285
00:14:58,252 --> 00:14:59,352
(Welcome. Is it your first time here?)

286
00:14:59,352 --> 00:15:00,752
Twinkle, twinkle!

287
00:15:02,719 --> 00:15:04,903
(Uncles play with him actively
to help him adjust.)

288
00:15:05,152 --> 00:15:06,652
(Uncle BEOMGYU jumps in.)

289
00:15:07,052 --> 00:15:08,185
(What?)

290
00:15:08,185 --> 00:15:09,219
You like it?

291
00:15:09,319 --> 00:15:11,952
(Embarrassed)

292
00:15:11,952 --> 00:15:13,785
(Uncle TAEHYUN brought
something interesting.)

293
00:15:13,785 --> 00:15:15,119
That looks so fun!

294
00:15:15,119 --> 00:15:16,119
(What's that?)

295
00:15:16,885 --> 00:15:18,019
That looks fun.

296
00:15:18,019 --> 00:15:19,619
(Running to the uncle
who gave the pacifier in the car)

297
00:15:19,619 --> 00:15:20,652
What's wrong?

298
00:15:20,752 --> 00:15:21,752
Do you want to ride that?

299
00:15:21,752 --> 00:15:23,319
(TAEHYUN is coming through.)

300
00:15:23,319 --> 00:15:25,485
(What is that?)

301
00:15:25,485 --> 00:15:27,685
It seems he feels safe with us.

302
00:15:27,685 --> 00:15:28,685
I know.

303
00:15:28,685 --> 00:15:30,819
You'll melt our hearts
when you look at us like that.

304
00:15:30,819 --> 00:15:32,085
(Yu Jun is shorter than a foam roller!)

305
00:15:32,219 --> 00:15:33,752
Shall we play the music now?

306
00:15:33,985 --> 00:15:35,919
- Let's start right away.
- Let's play it for him.

307
00:15:35,919 --> 00:15:37,085
We'll show you our dance.

308
00:15:37,619 --> 00:15:39,252
We're idols.

309
00:15:39,785 --> 00:15:40,785
You might not have noticed.

310
00:15:41,085 --> 00:15:43,552
Someday, you'll watch yourself
in the show and say,

311
00:15:43,552 --> 00:15:45,885
"Did we really film with them, Mom?"

312
00:15:46,619 --> 00:15:47,652
"But who are they?"

313
00:15:48,219 --> 00:15:49,419
"They're great dancers!"

314
00:15:49,419 --> 00:15:50,719
(Dancing in front of Yu Jun
for the first time)

315
00:15:50,719 --> 00:15:51,819
What an amazing dance!

316
00:15:52,719 --> 00:15:54,319
(Replacing with another song
due to copyright issues)

317
00:15:54,319 --> 00:15:55,819
We're perfectly in sync. Isn't he amazed?

318
00:15:55,819 --> 00:15:56,819
I know, right?

319
00:15:56,819 --> 00:15:59,619
(His eyes move fast in wonder.)

320
00:15:59,952 --> 00:16:01,419
How is it? We look so cool, right?

321
00:16:01,419 --> 00:16:05,419
(Time to watch the idol uncles at work)

322
00:16:08,719 --> 00:16:09,719
He looks at us on and off.

323
00:16:11,285 --> 00:16:12,452
We're dancing well, right?

324
00:16:13,819 --> 00:16:17,285
(First time seeing their footwork
in 14 months of his life)

325
00:16:17,819 --> 00:16:18,952
Great dance!

326
00:16:18,952 --> 00:16:21,052
- Let's clap!
- Clap!

327
00:16:21,619 --> 00:16:23,319
High five! They were so good.

328
00:16:23,919 --> 00:16:25,285
- All right!
- Yes!

329
00:16:25,285 --> 00:16:26,885
High five for Uncle BEOMGYU too.

330
00:16:27,219 --> 00:16:28,952
- Give Uncle BEOMGYU a high five.
- High five!

331
00:16:28,952 --> 00:16:30,919
High five for Uncle TAEHYUN too.
That's it!

332
00:16:30,919 --> 00:16:31,919
(Good job, Uncles.)

333
00:16:32,152 --> 00:16:34,385
- I think he liked it.
- He's feeling a bit better!

334
00:16:34,985 --> 00:16:35,985
He's smiling.

335
00:16:35,985 --> 00:16:36,985
He must have liked it.

336
00:16:36,985 --> 00:16:38,352
(I liked it!)

337
00:16:38,352 --> 00:16:40,119
How was the song?
Do you think it will be a hit?

338
00:16:40,452 --> 00:16:42,485
Hug HUENINGKAI
if you think it'll be successful.

339
00:16:42,885 --> 00:16:43,985
(Expecting a hit)

340
00:16:43,985 --> 00:16:46,219
He did it! He wasn't hugging him,
but then he did.

341
00:16:46,219 --> 00:16:47,285
If you think it will be a hit,

342
00:16:47,285 --> 00:16:48,492
- High five!
- High five!

343
00:16:48,493 --> 00:16:49,579
(TAEHYUN loves high-fives.)

344
00:16:49,619 --> 00:16:51,419
- It will go big!
- It will be successful!

345
00:16:51,585 --> 00:16:53,152
- He smiled.
- Wink if it will be a hit.

346
00:16:53,519 --> 00:16:54,519
Wink.

347
00:16:55,219 --> 00:16:56,219
Wink!

348
00:16:56,719 --> 00:16:57,819
(One more time!)

349
00:16:58,719 --> 00:16:59,719
We'll have a hit.

350
00:17:01,185 --> 00:17:07,152
(But it actually happened.)

351
00:17:07,585 --> 00:17:09,285
(Yu Jun also came to celebrate.)

352
00:17:09,285 --> 00:17:10,285
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

353
00:17:11,819 --> 00:17:13,552
(TXT dads)

354
00:17:13,752 --> 00:17:16,719
(But for now, they are top singers
who need to feed Yu Jun first.)

355
00:17:17,019 --> 00:17:19,852
(Top singer BEOMGYU plays with Yu Jun
using a plastic bag.)

356
00:17:19,852 --> 00:17:21,452
Here, Yu Jun. Eat it on your own.

357
00:17:22,719 --> 00:17:25,719
(He got an item!)

358
00:17:26,285 --> 00:17:27,385
You drop everything.

359
00:17:27,385 --> 00:17:28,385
I caught it on time.

360
00:17:30,419 --> 00:17:31,819
(I'll eat it myself.)

361
00:17:31,819 --> 00:17:33,219
Say, ah.

362
00:17:33,219 --> 00:17:35,919
(I can eat on my own
as long as I have my spoon!)

363
00:17:35,919 --> 00:17:36,919
He's eating well.

364
00:17:40,485 --> 00:17:41,519
Yu Jun, scoop it up and eat it.

365
00:17:41,519 --> 00:17:42,619
(One more bite after another)

366
00:17:42,619 --> 00:17:43,952
Delicious!

367
00:17:45,552 --> 00:17:46,552
Oops.

368
00:17:47,352 --> 00:17:48,352
Nice catch.

369
00:17:48,352 --> 00:17:50,085
That's it.

370
00:17:50,085 --> 00:17:51,552
Oh, no.

371
00:17:52,519 --> 00:17:53,752
- Foodie.
- Foodie.

372
00:17:55,052 --> 00:17:56,552
It's best not to open it beforehand.

373
00:17:56,552 --> 00:17:57,552
(Could that be?)

374
00:17:57,552 --> 00:17:59,285
- What?
- No, you have to eat.

375
00:17:59,285 --> 00:18:00,819
You should eat, Yu Jun.

376
00:18:00,819 --> 00:18:02,452
(Snack Detected)

377
00:18:02,452 --> 00:18:03,452
This?

378
00:18:04,085 --> 00:18:05,352
No, you don't!

379
00:18:05,652 --> 00:18:08,252
You're trying to eat this? No, Yu Jun.

380
00:18:08,252 --> 00:18:09,252
- Eat your meal.
- We'll give it after your meal.

381
00:18:09,252 --> 00:18:10,519
We'll give it if you eat all this.

382
00:18:11,952 --> 00:18:13,785
You can eat it after your meal.
There you go.

383
00:18:13,785 --> 00:18:15,685
(There are rice crackers!)

384
00:18:15,685 --> 00:18:16,752
No, you can't.

385
00:18:17,185 --> 00:18:18,385
- No means no.
- We've got something better.

386
00:18:18,719 --> 00:18:21,419
(No?)

387
00:18:21,419 --> 00:18:25,552
(Yu Jun's siren goes off.)

388
00:18:25,552 --> 00:18:27,252
You should eat your meal before dessert.

389
00:18:28,519 --> 00:18:30,019
(Bursting into tears)

390
00:18:30,019 --> 00:18:31,052
Why are you crying?

391
00:18:33,719 --> 00:18:36,619
(Eat first.)

392
00:18:36,619 --> 00:18:38,552
(Yummy!)

393
00:18:38,585 --> 00:18:40,385
- He should eat anyway.
- Eat this first.

394
00:18:40,385 --> 00:18:41,852
(Standing by to give cheese)

395
00:18:41,852 --> 00:18:43,619
- He's too tired to cry.
- Exactly.

396
00:18:43,985 --> 00:18:45,219
- That looks salty.
- Right.

397
00:18:45,219 --> 00:18:46,319
It's mixed with your tears.

398
00:18:46,552 --> 00:18:47,552
He must feel refreshed.

399
00:18:47,552 --> 00:18:49,785
(Mom, Dad, we had a great time
even when you were not around.)

400
00:18:49,785 --> 00:18:52,017
(He was about to cry, but stopped
when we let him look out the window.)

401
00:18:52,018 --> 00:18:53,924
(When he cried, we took a walk,
and he got better.)

402
00:18:53,925 --> 00:18:55,419
(Hehe, Yu Jun is sleeping!)

403
00:18:55,619 --> 00:18:58,385
(We also went to our practice room,
but we think he's afraid of a mirror.)

404
00:18:58,385 --> 00:19:00,530
(He got a bit scared since it was huge
with mirrors on all sides.)

405
00:19:00,531 --> 00:19:02,252
(He ate all the meal and snack today!)

406
00:19:02,252 --> 00:19:04,352
(We'll try more new things with Yu Jun!)

407
00:19:04,352 --> 00:19:06,885
(It's only our second time meeting,
but we're already closer.)

408
00:19:07,285 --> 00:19:08,685
- Who's this?
- Look who's here.

409
00:19:08,685 --> 00:19:09,719
Mom!

410
00:19:10,085 --> 00:19:11,152
You don't want to leave, right?

411
00:19:11,185 --> 00:19:12,685
Let's say hello to his dad.

412
00:19:12,752 --> 00:19:13,785
Geez!

413
00:19:14,252 --> 00:19:15,419
What?

414
00:19:16,019 --> 00:19:17,319
- All right.
- Oh, dear.

415
00:19:17,319 --> 00:19:18,552
We can't beat his parents.

416
00:19:18,952 --> 00:19:20,285
We're no match for them.

417
00:19:20,285 --> 00:19:22,694
- Gosh.
- Even his dad can't beat his mom.

418
00:19:23,552 --> 00:19:25,119
- No one can.
- He was an angel today.

419
00:19:25,652 --> 00:19:26,685
I mean it.

420
00:19:26,685 --> 00:19:28,319
He slept and ate well.

421
00:19:28,319 --> 00:19:29,452
- You suddenly feel great.
- Yu Jun!

422
00:19:30,685 --> 00:19:31,852
(Yu Jun acts cute with the uncles.)

423
00:19:31,852 --> 00:19:33,419
- He's happy all of a sudden.
- "I love you."

424
00:19:33,419 --> 00:19:35,619
- "I love you!"
- "I love you!"

425
00:19:35,952 --> 00:19:36,985
He's feeling better.

426
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:38,885
Say, "Hi."

427
00:19:39,085 --> 00:19:40,785
(Baby Yu Jun still likes
his mom the best.)

428
00:19:40,785 --> 00:19:41,852
That's it.

429
00:19:41,852 --> 00:19:43,085
"Hi!" Let's go.

430
00:19:43,319 --> 00:19:45,185
- Have a safe trip home, Yu Jun.
- Have a safe trip.

431
00:19:45,452 --> 00:19:47,019
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

432
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:48,752
(Uncles will see him again,
but they feel sad.)

433
00:19:48,752 --> 00:19:49,952
- Good work.
- Good work.

434
00:19:49,952 --> 00:19:51,319
- Have a safe trip home.
- Have a safe trip home.

435
00:19:51,319 --> 00:19:52,819
- Don't forget about us.
- "I love you!"

436
00:19:52,819 --> 00:19:54,919
- "I love you!"
- Right, don't forget.

437
00:19:54,919 --> 00:19:56,952
I'll keep my hair color.

438
00:19:58,345 --> 00:20:01,433
(7:40 a.m.: Meeting for the third time)

439
00:20:01,933 --> 00:20:04,733
(YEONJUN and SOOBIN are busy
making things early in the morning.)

440
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:08,200
(Making paper bricks for Yu Jun)

441
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:10,400
(His head shows how focused he is.)

442
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:12,533
I'm quite good at this.

443
00:20:13,166 --> 00:20:15,766
(Built for handmade work)

444
00:20:16,266 --> 00:20:17,900
You weren't here with us last time.

445
00:20:17,900 --> 00:20:20,300
To spend some fun time with Yu Jun,

446
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:22,466
- we tried to play with sand.
- You played with sand?

447
00:20:22,466 --> 00:20:23,633
But...

448
00:20:23,633 --> 00:20:25,000
he didn't really like it.

449
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,200
So we ended up playing by ourselves.

450
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:31,000
I'm not sure if he'll like this one.

451
00:20:32,066 --> 00:20:33,766
When is he coming? I can't wait.

452
00:20:34,566 --> 00:20:36,333
Since Yu Jun has seen us twice,

453
00:20:36,741 --> 00:20:41,476
he opened up to us
way more than the first time.

454
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,233
Did he recognize you, actually?

455
00:20:43,233 --> 00:20:45,200
I don't think he did.

456
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,333
(Feels like he's meeting them
for the first time)

457
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:49,466
But I think he might feel
more unfamiliar with you.

458
00:20:49,466 --> 00:20:51,600
But I was really clingy with him
last time,

459
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:52,633
so I think he'll recognize me.

460
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:55,475
(YEONJUN was clingy with him.)

461
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:58,633
(And again,
he got really clingy with him.)

462
00:20:58,633 --> 00:21:00,133
(What's with that guy?)

463
00:21:00,533 --> 00:21:01,966
(Turning away)

464
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:04,933
But weren't you
kind of one-sidedly clingy with him?

465
00:21:04,933 --> 00:21:06,766
He'll probably think,
"There he goes again."

466
00:21:10,366 --> 00:21:11,600
- Oh, my!
- He's here.

467
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:12,533
The baby is here.

468
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,448
- Is it him?
- I think it's him.

469
00:21:15,449 --> 00:21:16,800
(YEONJUN sprints out
to greet his little crush.)

470
00:21:17,133 --> 00:21:18,333
Good morning.

471
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,800
I think he's grown a bit
since I last saw him.

472
00:21:20,800 --> 00:21:21,733
That's right. He has.

473
00:21:22,566 --> 00:21:25,766
(Yu Jun arrives,
cutely holding a cracker.)

474
00:21:25,766 --> 00:21:28,066
Let me hold him.

475
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:29,766
- Yu Jun, see you.
- Say bye.

476
00:21:29,766 --> 00:21:31,800
He's about to cry.

477
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,000
Oh, my gosh.

478
00:21:33,366 --> 00:21:34,866
Oh, no. Yu Jun.

479
00:21:35,166 --> 00:21:37,233
- I'm sorry.
- See you later.

480
00:21:37,233 --> 00:21:38,066
Oh, my.

481
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,466
Take care.

482
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,666
It's all right.

483
00:21:41,666 --> 00:21:42,666
Yu Jun, I'm here, your mom.

484
00:21:43,066 --> 00:21:44,000
Your mom is here.

485
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,333
(Yu Jun, I'm Mommy YEONJUN.)

486
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:47,366
- You have your daddy too.
- I'm your mommy.

487
00:21:47,366 --> 00:21:48,966
- There's your daddy here too.
- Mom.

488
00:21:48,966 --> 00:21:49,866
Your mommy is here.

489
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:52,100
(Mom!)

490
00:21:53,766 --> 00:21:55,000
Want me to hold you?

491
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:56,400
Do you want to hold him?

492
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:58,100
(Yu Jun has no intention
of stopping his tears.)

493
00:21:58,933 --> 00:22:00,166
(Did he stop crying?)

494
00:22:00,566 --> 00:22:02,933
Try gently patting his back like this
to calm him down.

495
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,866
(Crying)

496
00:22:04,866 --> 00:22:06,566
Do you want to go to him?

497
00:22:06,566 --> 00:22:07,866
I'll take him.

498
00:22:07,866 --> 00:22:09,800
(Going into SOOBIN's familiar arms)

499
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:13,133
(YEONJUN's back looks a little down.)

500
00:22:13,133 --> 00:22:13,933
It's okay.

501
00:22:13,933 --> 00:22:15,133
(Stops crying
the moment he's with SOOBIN.)

502
00:22:15,133 --> 00:22:16,233
Want to look outside?

503
00:22:17,666 --> 00:22:20,033
He likes looking out the window.

504
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:21,300
Really? Oh, he stopped crying.

505
00:22:21,300 --> 00:22:22,500
I think he likes being outside.

506
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:23,600
(A one-day senior's childcare tip)

507
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,700
- Right?
- He's munching on a rice cracker.

508
00:22:26,566 --> 00:22:27,766
If you do this, he calms down quickly.

509
00:22:28,666 --> 00:22:30,833
(YEONJUN can only watch in envy.)

510
00:22:31,233 --> 00:22:34,200
(He worked hard and came back,
only to feel even more distant.)

511
00:22:35,166 --> 00:22:36,700
Should we cook for him?

512
00:22:37,366 --> 00:22:39,000
Yes. Can you cook, though?

513
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,600
(YEONJUN tries to make up for it
with breakfast.)

514
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:43,166
Do you know how to make scrambled eggs?

515
00:22:43,166 --> 00:22:44,933
Don't you just cook them in a pan?

516
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,400
(Doubtful eyes)

517
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:51,500
(Chef YEONJUN starts making breakfast.)

518
00:22:52,566 --> 00:22:54,700
- Do you know how to make scrambled eggs?
- I do.

519
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:55,966
(His expression is
that of a confident star chef.)

520
00:22:55,966 --> 00:22:57,000
I'm a bit worried.

521
00:22:57,828 --> 00:22:58,833
Do you want to cook?

522
00:22:58,833 --> 00:22:59,700
No, it's okay.

523
00:23:00,433 --> 00:23:01,733
I'm probably worse than you.

524
00:23:02,166 --> 00:23:06,033
(But despite what he said,
he looks skeptical.)

525
00:23:06,033 --> 00:23:08,366
(Keeping an eye on him)

526
00:23:08,700 --> 00:23:11,166
(Chef YEONJUN's menu: scrambled eggs)

527
00:23:11,433 --> 00:23:13,833
(Setting a frying pan first)

528
00:23:14,533 --> 00:23:16,233
I've never seen you cook before.

529
00:23:16,233 --> 00:23:19,966
(Maybe that's why he's already fumbling
just setting up the pan.)

530
00:23:20,133 --> 00:23:21,033
It's done.

531
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,666
(What's going on?)

532
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:28,800
(Next step is turning on
the induction stove)

533
00:23:30,566 --> 00:23:33,466
- Yu Jun might get bored today.
- Right.

534
00:23:33,466 --> 00:23:35,233
He's only got two guys to play with.

535
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:36,833
(Battling something on his own)

536
00:23:37,366 --> 00:23:38,366
What's wrong with this?

537
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:41,700
(No matter how much he yells at it,
the induction stove won't budge.)

538
00:23:42,066 --> 00:23:44,400
(His steps are getting faster,
feeling anxious.)

539
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,266
Done.

540
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:48,066
Yu Jun, just trust me.

541
00:23:48,466 --> 00:23:50,266
You know what I'm saying?

542
00:23:50,266 --> 00:23:51,433
He's cooking for you.

543
00:23:52,133 --> 00:23:53,600
Yu Jun, he says he'll make you eggs.

544
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:56,333
(Then, I'd better eat this now
just in case.)

545
00:23:56,833 --> 00:24:00,500
(Despite talking big, he still hasn't
even turned on the stove.)

546
00:24:00,700 --> 00:24:02,300
Is this actually working?

547
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:04,633
(His confidence is dropping fast.)

548
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,333
(His anxiety keeps rising.)

549
00:24:07,333 --> 00:24:08,500
I hear the sound, though.

550
00:24:08,966 --> 00:24:10,466
Yu Jun, I don't think
you're getting eggs today.

551
00:24:10,466 --> 00:24:12,333
(Laughing)

552
00:24:12,566 --> 00:24:14,733
(He finally turns on the stove
and starts cooking.)

553
00:24:16,533 --> 00:24:18,333
(The egg bursts in his hands.)

554
00:24:21,066 --> 00:24:23,766
(Anyone can tell
he's a complete beginner.)

555
00:24:23,766 --> 00:24:24,833
(Quickly looking around)

556
00:24:24,833 --> 00:24:26,133
(Trying to laugh it off)

557
00:24:26,133 --> 00:24:27,066
Hold on.

558
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,733
Yu Jun.

559
00:24:29,733 --> 00:24:30,700
Just trust me.

560
00:24:32,133 --> 00:24:33,633
Why is it stuck on the pan?

561
00:24:34,333 --> 00:24:35,700
I'll start it over.

562
00:24:37,500 --> 00:24:38,600
(Cracking)

563
00:24:38,933 --> 00:24:40,300
(This time, he smashes an egg
while taking it out.)

564
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:41,166
What's wrong with this?

565
00:24:41,866 --> 00:24:43,933
Maybe I can't control my strength
because it's morning.

566
00:24:43,933 --> 00:24:45,566
Gosh. Wait. This is insane.

567
00:24:45,966 --> 00:24:48,633
(Now, he's fighting the eggs.)

568
00:24:48,866 --> 00:24:51,166
Why does cooking eggs sound like
a whole disaster?

569
00:24:51,166 --> 00:24:53,166
These eggs break way too easily.

570
00:24:53,566 --> 00:24:54,633
(His suspicion turned into certainty.)

571
00:24:54,633 --> 00:24:56,866
I just picked one up, and it cracked.

572
00:24:58,333 --> 00:25:00,266
Just trust me.

573
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,566
It's never happened to me before.

574
00:25:02,566 --> 00:25:04,500
(The liar chef's "Just trust me,"
for the third time.)

575
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:07,866
(In the end, the two give up on breakfast
after waiting too long.)

576
00:25:08,766 --> 00:25:12,266
(Yu Jun turns his attention
to the paper bricks.)

577
00:25:13,066 --> 00:25:14,633
Try swinging the bricks.

578
00:25:14,633 --> 00:25:15,466
Like this.

579
00:25:15,466 --> 00:25:18,133
(Gently placing the brick back)

580
00:25:18,633 --> 00:25:20,033
How should I demonstrate this to him?

581
00:25:20,033 --> 00:25:21,366
(Babies aren't interested in
what others worked so hard to prepare)

582
00:25:21,366 --> 00:25:22,700
Yu Jun, look what I'm doing.

583
00:25:23,233 --> 00:25:24,133
Look at this.

584
00:25:24,366 --> 00:25:26,233
(The game builder steps in
to demonstrate himself)

585
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,000
Isn't it fascinating?

586
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,833
(No thanks.)

587
00:25:30,066 --> 00:25:31,066
Do you want to try it too?

588
00:25:31,066 --> 00:25:33,333
(Making him play with toys isn't easy.)

589
00:25:34,466 --> 00:25:38,133
(And for this man, cooking isn't easy.)

590
00:25:39,166 --> 00:25:41,866
It's my first time
making scrambled eggs for a baby.

591
00:25:42,266 --> 00:25:45,633
(The heat is on level 1,
and he doesn't know how to turn it up.)

592
00:25:45,633 --> 00:25:49,333
(His lips tighten in concentration.)

593
00:25:49,600 --> 00:25:52,166
(We're here to check again.)

594
00:25:52,166 --> 00:25:53,300
(Gasping)

595
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:55,100
(Is he doing it right?)

596
00:25:55,733 --> 00:25:56,800
Just trust me.

597
00:25:58,700 --> 00:25:59,933
I think he just laughed at me.

598
00:26:01,266 --> 00:26:04,466
(A scrambled egg does look laughable.)

599
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:06,733
Look at that.

600
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,300
This is egg porridge.

601
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:10,366
Are you sure about it?

602
00:26:10,366 --> 00:26:12,700
It just looks like this right now,

603
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:13,633
but it'll turn out fine.

604
00:26:13,900 --> 00:26:17,433
(Are you sure it'll turn out fine?)

605
00:26:17,433 --> 00:26:18,966
(The customers are leaving.)

606
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:25,100
(Will he be able
to feed him breakfast today?)
